The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on coherence modeling, which is a subfield of computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes novel methods that involve regression-based models and techniques for adding context, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its models based on metrics related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
